      "Interviews and reenactment conducted with witnesses"
    ],
    "summary": "On September 21, 2024, at approximately 1630 hours, a contract construction supervisor injured his right eye while familiarizing himself with a banding tool for heliport skirting repairs on the SM 160 A Facility. While holding the banding material housing with approximately 2 feet of material extended, a band clamp buckle slipped off the end. The banding material sprung forward, knocking off his safety glasses and striking his right eye with its sharp edge, lacerating the cornea. The CCS required evacuation and surgery.",
